ff5 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">than for your whole body to be thrown into hell&quot; (NIV). </div><div class="t m1ae x24 h1f y4d6 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Looking at life today. </div><div class="t m146 x24 h20 y4d7 ff5 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">• </div><div class="t m259 xa h20 y4d7 ff5 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How would you respond to the argument that a loving God would </div><div class="t m54 x24 h20 y2f1 ff5 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">never judge or condemn anyone? </div><div class="t m146 x24 h20 yac0 ff5 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">• </div><div class="t m7a xa h20 y88 ff5 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What .are some modern teachings (sincerely held by some Chris-</div><div class="t m23b x24 h20 yac1 ff5 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tians) that you believe God will condemn in the judgment?• Will He </div><div class="t m57 x24 h20 yac2 ff5 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">also condemn those who teach such views? What biblical evidence can </div><div class="t m165 x24 h20 yac3 ff5 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">you give for your answer? </div><div class="t m552 xcc h1f y4da ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">V. FREEDOM AND RESPONSIBILITY (Gal. 5:13-15). </div><div class="t mdf x7 h1f y4dc ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">13. </div><div class="t m12 x3a h1f y7a1 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How can Christians abuse freedom? Gal. 5:13. </div><div class="t m219 x2d h1f yac4 ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Law is a guide to freedom. </div><div class="t m543 x2c h20 yac4 ff5 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The New International Version says, </div><div class="t m88 x7 h20 yac5 ff5 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;You, my brothers, were called to be free. But do not use your freedom to </div><div class="t m3d1 x7 h20 yac6 ff5 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">indulge the sinful nature; rather, serve one another in love.&quot; This passage </div><div class="t m22f x7 h20 yac7 ff5 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">helps us to understand the proper relationship between law and faith. Law </div><div class="t m180 x7 h20 yac8 ff5 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">condemns those things that the sinful nature would lead us 